To serve a template based on an attribute assigned to an IP address and provide Server-Sent Events (SSE) for each template type using Node.js and Express.js, you can use the following code as a starting point:

```
const express = require('express');
const app = express();

// Define an array of IP addresses and their assigned template types
const ipTemplates = [
  { ip: '192.168.1.100', template: 'template1' },
  { ip: '192.168.1.101', template: 'template2' },
  { ip: '192.168.1.102', template: 'template3' }
];

// Define a function that gets the template type for a given IP address
function getTemplateType(ip) {
  const ipTemplate = ipTemplates.find(ipTemplate => ipTemplate.ip === ip);
  return ipTemplate ? ipTemplate.template : null;
}

// Set up a route that serves a template based on the assigned template type
app.get('/', (req, res) => {
  const ip = req.ip; // Get the IP address of the request
  const templateType = getTemplateType(ip); // Lookup the template type for the IP address
  if (templateType) {
    res.send(`This is ${templateType} template`);
  } else {
    res.send('Template not found');
  }
});

// Set up SSE for each template type
app.get('/sse/:templateType', (req, res) => {
  const templateType = req.params.templateType;
  res.set('Content-Type', 'text/event-stream');
  res.set('Cache-Control', 'no-cache');

  const intervalId = setInterval(() => {
    res.write(`data: This is an SSE message for ${templateType}\n\n`);
  }, 1000);

  req.on('close', () => {
    clearInterval(intervalId);
  });
});

// Start the server
app.listen(3000, () => {
  console.log('Server started on port 3000');
});
```

This code defines an array of IP addresses and their assigned template types, and provides a function to lookup the template type for a given IP address. It also sets up a route to serve a template based on the assigned template type, and another route to provide SSE for each template type.

When the root route is accessed (`/`), the code gets the IP address of the request and looks up the assigned template type for that IP address using the `getTemplateType` function. If a template type is found, the code sends a response with the appropriate template type, and if no template type is found, it sends a "Template not found" response.

When the SSE route is accessed (`/sse/:templateType`), the code sets the appropriate headers for SSE, and sends an SSE message every second with the template type specified in the route parameter. The `req.on('close')` callback ensures that the SSE messages are stopped when the client closes the connection.

